## What I Am Still Thinking About

One question I want to work through as the project continues: how do you document a continuous monitoring strategy in a way that is both comprehensive enough to be useful and concise enough to actually be read and used by the people responsible for executing it?

A 20-page monitoring strategy document is theoretically comprehensive but practically unlikely to be consulted during daily operations. A one-page summary is accessible but may miss important nuance. I think the answer involves a tiered documentation approach — a concise operational playbook for daily/weekly activities, supported by more detailed procedures for less frequent activities and incident response scenarios. But I want to think about what that looks like in practice.

